# Path of the Ancestral Guardian
Ancestral Protectors				KEY:Path of the Ancestral Guardian ~ Ancestral Protectors			CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Ancestral Guardian.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:While you're raging, you can use a bonus action on your turn to choose one creature you can see within 5 feet of you. Until the start of your next turn or until your rage ends, the chosen creature has disadvantage on any attack roll that doesn't target you, and if the creature takes the Disengage action within 5 feet of you, its speed is halved until the end of its turn.
Ancestral Shield					KEY:Path of the Ancestral Guardian ~ Ancestral Shield				CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Ancestral Guardian.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:If you are raging and an ally you can see within 30 feet of you takes bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage, you can use your reaction to transfer your resistance to those damage types to the ally. The resistance applies to the incoming damage. Until the start of your next turn, the ally keeps the resistance and you lack it, unless you also have it from a source other than Rage.
Consult the Spirits					KEY:Path of the Ancestral Guardian ~ Consult the Spirits			CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Ancestral Guardian.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:Right before you make an Intelligence or a Wisdom check, you can give yourself advantage on the check. You can use this feature three times, and you regain expended uses when you finish a long rest.
Vengeful Ancestors					KEY:Path of the Ancestral Guardian ~ Vengeful Ancestors				CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Ancestral Guardian.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:When you or an ally you can see within 30 feet of you is damaged by a melee attack while you're raging, you can use your reaction to cause the attacker to take 2d8 force damage from the spirits.

# Path of the Storm Herald
Storm of Fury			KEY:Path of the Storm Herald ~ Storm of Fury		CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Storm Herald.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:When you select this path at 3rd level, choose one of the following options: desert, sea, or tundra. The environment you choose shapes the nature of the storm you conjure when you rage. While raging, you emanate an aura in a 10-foot radius. The effects of this aura depend on your chosen environment.	DESC:Desert. Any enemy that ends its turn in your aura takes fire damage equal to %1.|floor(2+BarbarianLVL/4)|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Storm Herald Choice ~ Desert		DESC:Sea. At the end of each of your turns, you can choose a creature in your aura, other than yourself. The target must make a Dexterity saving throw against a DC equal to %1. The target takes %2d6 lightning damage on a failed save, and half as much damage on a successful one.|8+Proficiency_Bonus+CON|Storm_of_Fury_Sea_Damage|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Storm Herald Choice ~ Sea	DEFINE:Storm_of_Fury_Sea_Damage|0	BONUS:VAR|Storm_of_Fury_Sea_Damage|2+(BarbarianLVL>=10)+(BarbarianLVL>=15)	DESC:Tundra. Any enemy that ends its turn in your aura takes cold damage equal to %1.|floor(2+BarbarianLVL/4)|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Storm Herald Choice ~ Tundra		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Storm Herald Choice|1	
