# Path of the Zealot
Divine Fury				KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Divine Fury				CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:You can channel divine fury when you start to rage. If you do so, you become cloaked in an aura of divine power until the rage ends. At the end of each of your turns for that duration, each creature within 5 feet of you takes damage equal to 1d6 + %1. The damage is necrotic or radiant; you choose the type of damage when you gain this feature.|BarbarianLVL/2
Warrior of the Gods		KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Warrior of the Gods		CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:If a spell would have the sole effect of restoring you to life (but not undeath), the caster does not need material components to cast the spell on you.
Zealous Focus			KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Zealous Focus				CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:If you fail a saving throw while raging, you can instead succeed on that saving throw as a reaction. However, doing so immediately ends your rage, and you can't rage again until you finish a short or long rest.
Zealous Presence		KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Zealous Presence			CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:As an action, you howl in fury and unleash a battle cry infused with divine energy. Every ally within 60 feet of you gains advantage on attack rolls and saving throws until the start of your next turn. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.
Rage Beyond Death		KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Rage Beyond Death			CATEGORY:Special Ability		TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality.Class Feature		DESC:While raging, having 0 hit points doesn't knock you unconscious. You still must make death saving throws, and you suffer the normal effects of taking damage while at 0 hit points. However, if you would die due to failing death saving throws, you don't die until your rage ends.